SUMMARY:College Park Climate Action Neighborhood and Gardens Gone Native
DESCRIPTION:Food Forests support natural ecosystems\, improving the quality of our air\, soil and waterways\, while connecting our communities with nature and nourishment.  Join panelists Aidan Fife of RegenAll; Clair Kauffman of Fruitful Backyards;  Elyse Jurgen\, Waxwing Echoworks; and Michael Meyer\, City of Lancaster Urban Forester as they discuss Lancaster’s Urban Forest and how we can all support the sustainable development of food forests in our city.  Presented by College Park Climate Action Neighborhood and Gardens Gone Native. 
URL:https://visitlancastercity.com/event/college-park-climate-action-neighborhood-and-gardens-gone-native/
